# Next.js App Router

## Server vs Client

```
Needs useState/useEffect/events?  → 'use client'
Needs browser APIs?               → 'use client'
Just renders data?                → Server Component (default)
Both?                             → Server parent + Client leaf
```

Never add `'use client'` out of habit. Push it to the leaves.

## Data fetching

```ts
// ✅ Parallel
const [users, posts] = await Promise.all([getUsers(), getPosts()])

// ✅ Stream slow data
<Suspense fallback={<Skeleton />}>
  <SlowComponent />
</Suspense>

// ✅ Next.js 15 — params/searchParams are async (BREAKING)
const Page = async ({ params }: { params: Promise<{ id: string }> }) => {
  const { id } = await params
}

// ✅ cookies/headers are async (BREAKING)
const cookieStore = await cookies()
```

## Server Actions

```ts
'use server'
export const createItem = async (formData: FormData) => {
  await db.items.create({ data: { name: formData.get('name') as string } })
  revalidatePath('/items')
}
```

## Performance

- `dynamic()` for heavy client components
- `next/image` — never `<img>`
- `next/link` — never `<a>` for internal nav
- `import 'server-only'` for server-only modules
- Direct imports over barrel files for large libs

## Anti-patterns

| ❌ Don't | ✅ Do |
|---|---|
| `useEffect` for fetch | Server Component or TanStack Query |
| Sequential awaits on independent fetches | `Promise.all()` |
| `'use client'` on layouts or pages | Push to leaf components |
| `params.id` without awaiting | `const { id } = await params` |
| `<img>` | `next/image` |
| `<a>` for internal links | `next/link` |
